-- mixed-hard-soft.cell: proof-carrying computation exercise
-- Demonstrates Cell's killer pattern: LLM solves (NP), code verifies (P).
--
-- This program has three cells on the crystallization spectrum:
--   solve     (вЉұ  soft)  вЂ” LLM finds x such that 2x+3=11
--   substitute (вЉұ= hard) вЂ” deterministic substitution check
--   explain   (вЉұ  soft)  вЂ” LLM interprets the result
--
-- The hard cell (substitute) catches wrong answers that the soft
-- cells might produce. This is proof-carrying computation:
-- the proof (verification) is cheaper than the search.

вЉұ solve
  given equation в‰Ұ "2x + 3 = 11"
  yield x, proof[]

  в€ө Solve В«equationВ» for x. Show your work as В«proofВ» (list of steps).

  вЉЁ x is a number

вЉұ= substitute
  given solveв†’x
  given equation в‰Ұ "2x + 3 = 11"
  yield holds

  вЉұ= holds в†ђ eval(2 * solveв†’x + 3) = 11

  вЉЁ holds = true

вЉұ explain
  given solveв†’x
  given solveв†’proof
  given substituteв†’holds
  yield explanation

  в€ө If В«substituteв†’holdsВ» is true, explain the solution В«solveв†’proofВ» in plain English.
    If false, say "The solution x=В«solveв†’xВ» is WRONG because substitution failed."

  вЉЁ explanation mentions the value of x
  вЉЁ if substituteв†’holds then explanation is positive
